paragraphs.title: Save SITE dataframe in a DB table
paragraphs.text:
%python

cr = oml.cursor()

try:

  oml_df = oml.create(site_df, table='SITE_OPERATION_COST_REVENUE')
  print("Table Created !!")
 
except Exception as e:
  print("Exception occured and handled:",e)
  
  query = "TRUNCATE table SITE_OPERATION_COST_REVENUE"
  cr.execute(query)
  
  try:
    oml_df = oml.create(site_df, table='SITE_OPERATION_COST_REVENUE', append=True)
    print("Records Updated !!")
    
  except Exception as a:
  
    print("Exception occured and handled :", a)
    oml_df = oml.create(site_df, table='SITE_OPERATION_COST_REVENUE')
    print("Records Updated !!")
  
finally:
    z.show(oml_df)

Making a copy of Existed and New development sites
Convert Lat Long degree into radeon
paragraphs.text:
%python
for column in SITE_LOCATION[["LATITUDE", "LONGITUDE"]]:

    SITE_LOCATION[f'{column}_rad'] = rad
    
for column in NEW_SITE_LOCATION[["LATITUDE", "LONGITUDE"]]:

    NEW_SITE_LOCATION[f'{column}_rad'] = rad

paragraphs.title: Make a Ball tree of existing Site location and query against new development sites
paragraphs.text:
%python
ball = BallTree(SITE_LOCATION[["LATITUDE_rad", "LONGITUDE_rad"]].values, metric='haversine')


neighbours = 5


distances, indices = ball.query(NEW_SITE_LOCATION[["LATITUDE_rad", "LONGITUDE_rad"]].values, k = neighbours)
# indices= indices[:,1:]
# distances = distances[:,1:]

paragraphs.title: Indexes of Nearest neighbors from each New development site
Distance of Nearest neighbors from each New development site
Convert distance value to Kilometers
Calculate Total cost and Total Revenue of New sites based on its Nearest neighbors
paragraphs.text:
%python
def Predict_Total_Cost_Revenue(indices, SITE_LOCATION, neighbours):
    
    neighbour_list = [SITE_LOCATION.iloc[idx] for idx in indices]
    predicted_cost = [sum(i['COST'])/(neighbours) for i in neighbour_list]
    predicted_revenue = [sum(i['REVENUE'])/(neighbours) for i in neighbour_list]
    return predicted_cost, predicted_revenue, neighbour_list


Y1, Y2, neighbour_list = Predict_Total_Cost_Revenue(indices, SITE_LOCATION, neighbours)
new_site_df['TOTAL_COST'] = Y1
new_site_df['TOTAL_REVENUE'] = Y2
z.show(new_site_df)

paragraphs.title: For each New Development sites, store the information of its Nearest Neighbor in the dataframe
paragraphs.text:
%python
def Nearest_neighbour_table(NEAREST_NEIGHBOR_DF, neighbour_list, distances, neighbours):
    
    NEAREST_NEIGHBOR_DF['NEAREST_SITE_ID'] = [j for i in range(len(neighbour_list)) for j in (neighbour_list[i]['SITE_ID'])]
    
    NEAREST_NEIGHBOR_DF['NEAREST_SITE_NAME'] = [y for x in range(len(neighbour_list)) for y in (neighbour_list[x]['NAME'])]
    
    NEAREST_NEIGHBOR_DF['DISTANCE'] = [round(km,2) for km in distances.flatten()]
    
    NEAREST_NEIGHBOR_DF['DEVELOPMENT_NAME'] = [values[2] for values in new_site_df.values for dev_name in range(neighbours)]
    
    NEAREST_NEIGHBOR_DF['DEVELOPMENT_ROLLOUT_ID'] = [values[0] for values in new_site_df.values for dev_name in range(neighbours)]
    
    NEAREST_NEIGHBOR_DF['LATITUDE'] = [lat for value in range(len(neighbour_list)) for lat in (neighbour_list[value]['LATITUDE'])]
    
    NEAREST_NEIGHBOR_DF['LONGITUDE'] = [long for value in range(len(neighbour_list)) for long in (neighbour_list[value]['LONGITUDE'])]

Nearest_neighbour_table(NEAREST_NEIGHBOR_DF, neighbour_list, distances, neighbours)

paragraphs.title: Save NEAREST NEIGHBOR dataframe in a DB table
paragraphs.text:
%python

cr = oml.cursor()

try:

  oml_df3 = oml.create(NEAREST_NEIGHBOR_DF, table='NEAREST_NEIGHBOR')
  print("Table Created !!")
 
except Exception as e:
  print("Exception occured and handled:",e)
  
  query = "TRUNCATE table NEAREST_NEIGHBOR"
  cr.execute(query)
  
  try:
    oml_df3 = oml.create(NEAREST_NEIGHBOR_DF, table='NEAREST_NEIGHBOR', append=True)
    print("Records Updated !!")
    
  except Exception as a:
  
    print("Exception occured and handled:", a)
    oml_df3 = oml.create(NEAREST_NEIGHBOR_DF, table='NEAREST_NEIGHBOR')
    print("Records Updated !!")
